gameData

Class LineupSlot

  • java.lang.Object
    • gameData.LineupSlot

  • public class LineupSlot
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is meant to simulate a baseball lineup in the game MLB Showdown. In a lineup, each player occupies a spot in the order, 1st through 9th, and plays a position in the field, the 8 hitting field positions and either a DH or a Pitcher depending on AL or NL. This version of MLB Showdown at the moment is only meant to support AL Rules.

    .1
    Author:
    Matthew
